.TH KMEM_ALLOC 9 "@PACKAGE_DATE@" "@PACKAGE@-@VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_TITLE@ DDI/DKI"
.SH NAME
.B kmem_alloc
\- allocate kernel memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.B #include <sys/kmem.h>
.HP
.BI "void *" ptr " = kmem_alloc(size_t " size ", int " flags );
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I size
the size of memory to allocate.
.TP
.I flags
how to allocate the memory.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Requests that the number of bytes of kernel memory specified by the argument
.I size
be allocated with the options specified by
.I flags
and returned as a
.I ptr
to the allocated memory.
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.PP
.BR kmem_alloc ()
returns a pointer to the alocated memory on success.  On failure,
.BR kmem_alloc ()
returns a
.B NULL
pointer.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
When
.BR kmem_alloc ()
fails to allocate the requested memory, it returns a
.B NULL
pointer.
.SH CAVEATS
The LiS
.[
LiS
.]
version of
.BR kmem_alloc ()
ignores the
.I flags
argument an always allocates using
.I Linux
.BR GFP_ATOMIC .
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR kmem_zalloc (9),
.BR kmem_free (9).
